TITLE: Mother's Day can be painful. These strategies might help
SUMMARY: Mother's Day can be a painful time, especially for people living with loss. Author Rebecca Soffer shares ideas for how to care for yourself or loved ones on a difficult day.

TITLE: An appeals court reinstates portions of Florida's new election law
SUMMARY: A federal appeals court granted Florida's request to reinstate parts of the state's election law while it appeals a lower court's decision that the law was aimed at suppressing Black voters.

TITLE: 'Mama's boy' is a flex, not an insult, for a new generation of men
SUMMARY: For eons, the term "mama's boy" was widely viewed as an emasculating insult. But numerous men are challenging such inherent misogyny and publicly embracing their identities as proud "mama's boys."

TITLE: From stalkers to saints, moms run the gamut in kids' books
SUMMARY: Children's books depict a range of maternal styles. For this Mother's Day, we asked some experts to weigh in on some classics and offer recommendations.

TITLE: The good times are rolling for Big Oil. 3 things to know about their surging profits
SUMMARY: Major energy companies have reported a surge in profits in the first three months of the year as oil prices have rallied.

TITLE: GOP playbook on abortion is to push Democrats on restrictions and contort their words
SUMMARY: Republicans are trying to shift and deflect attention away from the Supreme Court's conservative majority weighing the overturning of <em>Roe v. Wade

TITLE: Missouri U.S. House candidates hit the campaign trail without set districts or voters
SUMMARY: Missouri congressional candidates have no idea where to campaign or which voters to court. That's because, with just months to go until the primary, GOP state lawmakers can't decide on a voting map.

TITLE: A Michigan law from 1931 would make abortion a felony if Roe falls
SUMMARY: The law could put doctors, and even patients, in prison for up to four years. And the state's attorney general says she can't stop local prosecutors from enforcing it.

TITLE: Federal labor officials accuse Starbucks of unfair labor practices in Buffalo
SUMMARY: A National Labor Relations Board official outlined a host of labor law violations in a filing seeking reinstatement and backpay for the employees.

SUMMARY: A variety of items will be tax-free in the state over coming months. The move comes as Americans are facing soaring inflation and high gas prices.

TITLE: Coronavirus FAQ: Should I go to that party? What do I do if guests got COVID?
SUMMARY: Whether it's a wedding, graduation or meeting, indoor events can spread the virus. Here's a complete guide: what to ponder before going, how to cut risks while there, what to do if cases crop up.

SUMMARY: Abortion-rights advocates have seen an outpouring of support since the Supreme Court's draft decision to overturn <em>Roe v. Wade

TITLE: A car linked to an Alabama escapee and jail worker has been found
SUMMARY: The car was found in an impound lot in Tennessee, where it sat for nearly a week before authorities realized they had it, officials said Friday.

TITLE: Russia-Ukraine war: What happened today (May 6)
SUMMARY: A roundup of key developments and the latest in-depth coverage of Russia's invasion of Ukraine.

TITLE: YouTuber and self-appointed relationship guru Kevin Samuels, dead at 56
SUMMARY: Atlanta police confirmed that Samuels was found unresponsive on the floor of his apartment. Samuels was famous for his takes on dating and relationships.
